---
source: crates/ridge-lexer/tests/snapshots.rs
expression: render(GAME_OF_LIFE)
---
0..421 DOC_COMMENT "Conway's Game of Life on a fixed 20x40 grid.  A pure `step` function advances\nthe simulation; I/O and timing are isolated to the main loop.  The grid is\nrepresented as a record `{ rows, cols, cells }` so width and height travel with\nthe data without extra parameters at every call site.  Main initialises with a\nglider, prints each frame at 200 ms intervals, and runs for N generations\n(N from argv, default 30)."
